<li><a href="http://oig.hhs.gov/fraud/enforcement/criminal/index.asp#CEA2015013003">http://oig.hhs.gov/fraud/enforcement/criminal/index.asp#CEA2015013003</a></li>
<li><a href="http://oig.hhs.gov/fraud/enforcement/criminal/index.asp#CEA2015020503">http://oig.hhs.gov/fraud/enforcement/criminal/index.asp#CEA2015020503</a></li>
</ul>
</p>
<p><a href="http://www.justice.gov/usao/txe/News/2015/edtx-hcf-yusuf-020215.html ">A former OIG Most Wanted fugitive, Vivian Yusuf</a>, was jailed for more than seven years in a multimillion-dollar medical supplies scam in Texas. Yusuf had been on the run for several years before her capture in Houston in 2014.</p>
<p><a href="http://oig.hhs.gov/fraud/enforcement/criminal/index.asp#CEA2015020501">And the new Connecticut Public Corruption Task Force</a>, which includes OIG, will investigate corruption, fund misuse and other crimes in the state.</p>
<p>For links to these reports and stories and more, go to our website or follow us on Twitter.</p>
<p>And for more on the fight against health care fraud, waste and abuse, click "More News" on the podcast webpage.</p>
<p>Thanks for listening.</p>




